I"Ê<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/joint-marginal-and-conditional-probabilities-are-primitives-of-probability-theory">Probability</a> density functions (PDFs) link <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/continuous-state-dynamical-systems-share-a-common-structure">continuous</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-a-certain-anatomy">states</a> <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/boltzmann-distribution-links-macrostates-with-microstate-probabilities">with probabilities</a>. However, deriving probabilies using PDFs only works for intervals. In contrast, <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/joint-marginal-and-conditional-probabilities-are-primitives-of-probability-theory">probability</a> mass functions (PMFs) map <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/finite-state-dynamical-systems-are-diverse">finite state sets</a> to probabilities which are meaningful for both single states and subsets.</p>
